Content:
I've been working through "Groups and Symmetry" (Armstrong) and came across this problem in chapter 9 which I can't figure out. Any hints/help would be greatly appreciated! Show that every $2\times 2$ unitary matrix has the form $$
\left(\begin{array}{c c}
w & z \\
-e^{i \theta} z^{*} & e^{i \theta} w^{*}
\end{array}\right)
$$ for some $\theta\in\mathbb{R}$ and $w,z\in\mathbb{C}$. (A matrix is said to be unitary if it is invertible with its adjoint as the inverse. The symbol "*" denotes complex conjugate.)
